<p><strong>Item#:</strong> SCP-MtIW</p>
<p><strong>Object Class:</strong> Safe</p>
<p><strong>Special Containment Procedures:</strong> SCP-MtIW is not allowed internet or local network access. Access to SCP-MtIW is restricted to level 3 classification. Before examining SCP-MtIW, personnel is required to disconnect their computer from the network.</p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> SCP-MtIW is a digital file labeled &quot;MeettheInterviewer-WhiteGuard.doc&quot;. A Foundation junior researcher discovered the file after an anonymous user posted a download link to it on a Parawatch forum. SCP-MtIW displays the ability to self-update regardless of whether the internet or any other network access is available. The contents of the file include references to the Foundation as a fictional organization documented by a web-based collaborative-fiction project. Linked references to SCPs within SCP-MtIW correlate to a number of known SCPs under our custody. When accessing the respective link for each of these SCPs, Foundation files for the given entity will be displayed. It is currently unknown as to how SCP-MtIW accomplishes its self-updating procedure, how it is aware of our existence, and how it has complete access to our otherwise secure files.</p>
